    <section>
      <title>Introduction</title>
      <content>
        <para>YALLA is Yet Another Logging Library Abstraction for .NET.</para>
        <para>
          <mediaLink>
            <image xlink:href="Yalla" placement="center" />
            <caption lead="Figure 1" placement="after">Deployment diagram</caption>
          </mediaLink>
        </para>
      </content>
    </section>

    <section>
      <title>Supported Platforms</title>
      <content>
        <para>
          <list class="bullet">
            
            <listItem>.NET Framework 4</listItem>
            
            <listItem>Silverlight 5</listItem>
            
            <listItem>
              Windows 8 <legacyItalic>(WIP)</legacyItalic>
            </listItem>
            
            <listItem>
              Windows Phone 8.1 <legacyItalic>(WIP)</legacyItalic>
            </listItem>

            <listItem>
              Windows Phone Silverlight 8 <legacyItalic>(WIP)</legacyItalic>
            </listItem>
            
            <listItem>
              Xamarin.Android <legacyItalic>(WIP)</legacyItalic>
            </listItem>
            
            <listItem>
              Xamarin.iOS <legacyItalic>(WIP)</legacyItalic>
            </listItem>
            
            <listItem>
              Xamarin.OSX <legacyItalic>(WIP)</legacyItalic>
            </listItem>
            
            <listItem>Portable Class Libraries</listItem>
            
          </list>
        </para>
        <para>
          <alert class="note">
            <para>
              <legacyBold>This is a preliminary release with limited functionality.</legacyBold>
              .NET Framework 4 (and later), Silverlight 5 and Portable Class Libraries are the only platforms that are currently supported.
            </para>
          </alert>
        </para>
      </content>
    </section>

    <section>
      <title>Getting Started</title>
      <content>

        <para>
          As shown in Figure 1 above, YALLA supports a variety of use cases, which include the following:
          <list class="ordered">
            <listItem>
              <para>
                <newTerm>Application Code Input:</newTerm>
                Your application code either requires the addition of logging functionality, or has logging functionality that requires modification.
              </para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>
                <newTerm>Library Code Input:</newTerm>
                Your library code either requires the addition of logging functionality, or has logging functionality that requires modification.
              </para>
            </listItem>
            <listItem>
              <para>
                <newTerm>Platform Facility Output:</newTerm>
                Your application or library code requires its logging functionality to use one or more platform-specific output facilities.
              </para>
            </listItem>
          </list>
        </para>

        <para>
          <alert class="note">
            <para>
              <legacyBold>This is a preliminary release with limited functionality.</legacyBold>
              <legacyItalic>Application Code Input</legacyItalic>, <legacyItalic>Library Code Input</legacyItalic> and <legacyItalic>Platform Facility Output</legacyItalic>
              are the only use cases that are currently supported.
            </para>
          </alert>
        </para>
        
        <para>
          You only need to add the
          <externalLink>
            <linkUri>http://yalladotnet.github.io/Yalla.Core</linkUri>
            <linkText>YALLA Core Library</linkText>
          </externalLink>
          as a dependency to your project in order to apply the
          <legacyItalic>Application Code Input</legacyItalic>
          use case or the
          <legacyItalic>Library Code Input</legacyItalic>
          use case.
          The YALLA Core Library documentation contains installation instructions and relevant API reference.
        </para>
        
        <para>
          In order for your application to produce YALLA log(s),
          you need to add YALLA as a dependency to the main project(s)
          (The YALLA Core Library dependency will be added for you.).
          If you haven't already, install the
          <externalLink>
            <linkUri>https://www.nuget.org/packages/Yalla</linkUri>
            <linkText>YALLA NuGet package</linkText>
          </externalLink>.
          The current version is <link xlink:href="cf8fbd97-3f79-4c3b-a626-d7545a36d3e4" />.
        </para>

        <para>
          The logging system must be properly initialized at application startup.
          The recommended method is
          <codeEntityReference>M:Yalla.IConfigurationSource.Configure</codeEntityReference>.
        </para>

        <para>
          The logging system must be properly terminated at application teardown.
          The recommended method is
          <codeEntityReference>M:Yalla.LogManager.Shutdown</codeEntityReference>.
        </para>

        <para>Detailed YALLA API information may be found in the Reference section.</para>
        
      </content>
